caption: I love this place, excellent food & service. Definitely worth a return trip. The bill was decent for the quality. Feels like a place in Los Angeles I liked.
Fine
Was once a great place for food and drink. No just a shell of its self. Sad.
This has got to be the best fish and chips around. We've been going up there since the 1980's... I don't blink an eye to drive and hour and a half from Lafayette, Indiana to Chicago to eat there.
On the advice of sir Ruggy (who has never yet set me astray), I came down here for some mid-sketchfest booze to keep the day flowing if ya know what I mean.
Excellent food and atmosphere. It is very authentic  WWI era English Pub
Perfect ambiance to grab a beer on a cold winter's night with some friends. Not too loud, not too quiet. This is a great bar.

Very fine place with a lot of English flavor particularly related to two wars World War One and Two!Lots of interesting tidbits if you have a chance to talk to the owner! Great food and fantastic selection of spirits!!!Exelent service!!!
Old European charm, simple menu, good fish and chips

One of the best places in Chicago for exceptionally English-Style beer, delicious pub food, and even better conversation. The owner, Colin, never fails in making us feel like family as he splits his time between running a tight ship and seemingly performing a one man comedy show. As far as the ambience is concerned, I doubt that you could find a more intimately comfortable and whimsically decorated establishment in the states. The Whisky selection is so vast it can hardly be contained to a parcel aptly named “The Book of Life”. They have an exceptionally good fish and chips & the Wells Bombardier is a seriously good brew. Pay them a visit and hope that Colin and/or Jordan are behind the bar.
Food and drinks were great. Loved the hambuger, scott egg, fish and chips.

I have passed this place so many times and I was not disappointed when I finally went in. Super cozy atmosphere with great drink and food options. I had a cranberry cider and shepherd's pie, which were both delicious. I think I'll be coming more often.
Try the Bananas Foster

Great place, I love it. Incredible food with an even more incredible atmosphere. The assortment of drinks and beers on top is incredible and the service is fantastic. A very lively place to enjoy a meal.
Recently came in for dinner and waited 10 minutes to be seated then we waited 15 mins with no service so we left. Also, staff is extremely rude. Would not recommend.
The food was great, exactly what you'd expect from the description. The waiter we had was incredibly friendly. Food took a bit long to come out but it was still a very pleasant experience.
Pure class!
Good food and good beer. The bartender that we had was really nice. If I am in the area again, I will stop.

Downright hostile waiter started by not acknowledging our reservation. Told us that we had better not take photos of him, which of course we were not doing. Made us put away birthday cake for our event. Had no idea who ordered what drink. Made fun of member of our party who didn't drink. Stopped by table four times to say that we shouldn't try to split the check. At a certain point we decided to switch bars and waiter expressed anger that we were not ordering food. Beautiful bar, but not recommended.
Unbelievably rich in military history.  Beautiful place and the most knowledgable staff
Great atmosphere. What you want an Irish pub to feel like.
Terrible service. Took forever to get food. Food was mediocre.
The bartender was the owner I think, and he's amazing. Awesome beer, didn't get to try the food though. Ask the bartender about the artwork his father made (if you meet him)
Great place

The ambiance here is fantastic - I love the library!  They were SUPER busy, but the service was still quick and courteous.  Skip the curry fries - they're just regular fries with some curry seasoning sprinkled on top.  The corned beef sandwich was awesome.
Great services. Great cocktail. Affordable prices.
The most magnificent bar ever and Colin is the best. This place is magical.
Atmosphere and service. Conversation rules here. Colin is a first-class raconteur.
Authentic British pub in the heart of Chicago! Excellent selection of drafts and bottles from the UK, accompanied with authentic British pub food! Try their Scotch egg!
Nice vibe, good selection of drinks
Cozy and unique bar. Great for a few drinks wirh friends to catch up
Great pub. Small menu but is genuine and authentic. An extremely cozy bar
Very welcoming - a great place to spend an evening, alone at the bar or with friends.
Great food, amazing atmosphere, most beautiful interior of a pub I've been to. Good service on top of that. The scotch eggs are stunningly good
Great decor, (library and ww1) good vibe traditional pub type food good beer selection. Fun for a late meal or a place hang out and have a beer.
Cool fun low key environment with great drink prices, fun to gather with friends!
Great British style pub with great food and a very authentic selection of British beers
Probably the best pub in Chicago, definitely the best shepherd pie
The food and atmosphere were excellent, but there was only 2 hosts taking care of the whole pub, so even placing drink or food orders took a long time let alone getting your food. Needs more staff.
Great food. Friendly staff. Authentic experience.
the atmosphere of this place is awesome, bartenders take care of you

Second year in a row for our Anniversary dinner. Love the decor and overall experience. My wife and I spent some time in London and Ireland and this place really captures the spirit of any pub/inn that we visited there. Highly recommend.

I can not say enough nice things about this place. We had a party of 12 people. The atmosphere is great. The food was wonderful. The owner is very nice and kept checking in our party to make sure we had everything. If you are in the area you need to stop in. Free parking on Sundays.

The guy who sat/served us was great. Had a number of big parties the night we came in and still managed to provide great service and I got to have a scotch egg for the very first time! The space is beautiful and it was a great spot.

Excellent atmosphere - E comfortable English pub feel with lots of authentic WWII-themed wall art and excellent lighting. Okay service, wide range of ciders, scotches, and a decent list of imported beers. Food seemed adequate (only ordered brussel sprouts, but was very good for any place called a pub) and service was competent, albeit salty.

This is a very unique place.  Beautiful archtecture.  The walls are filled with the memories of veterans and the history of their stories.  Food and drinks served later.  Good place to stop after a play.

The Red Lion Pub is a great place to visit! It has a great atmosphere. I felt like I was sitting inside of Colin’s study with his collection of books, art pieces, and liquor. The owner, Colin, was nothing short of amazing. He’s knowledgeable, has a lot of great stories, and makes a mean cocktail. I highly recommend this pub!
The shepherd's pie was awesome! The staff was very friendly and it was great to see all the military memorabilia.
Excellent Shepard's pie and Breakfast Poutine!  Very friendly staff!  Will definately come back here again.  So much military history here.
Food was outstanding,  service excellent and the environment was fascinating!
Laid back atmosphere. Good happy hour special. Unique beer selection.
Try the shepherd's pie

Great vibe! Attentive bartenders. Owner, Colin, is often there telling stories, referencing old movies and explaining all the wonderful memorabilia that fills this cozy yet spacious pub. Good food as well! Must see!

Unique atmosphere. A pub filled with books. Took my d&d group here for my birthday because I thought they'd appreciate the aesthetic and I was right. Service was good, food was good, and it was a night to remember.
Scotch eggs and Shepherd's Pie were Amazing!   Great pub atmosphere! Definitely coming back to try more dishes.
Terrible service, plastic forks, and 20% tip added to table of 4 without notice.
Beautiful pub.  We stopped here on beer tasting tour, would look forward to spending a full day enjoying more of what they have to offer.

Visited last night, for the first time. Having walks Down Lincoln Avenue past numerous loud College bars it was a relief to pop my head into the Red Lion will be greeted by soft lowlights and a gentle murmur of friends chatting.  It's as though we were transported back to a dingy little hole-in-the-wall bar on the outskirts of London.  Excellent whiskey selection, very European focused beer list. Poutine was super salty but delicious.  A snack and far too many rounds put us back less than a hundred bucks... We will be back again soon.
Beautiful! Great selection.
One of One English Pub!  Amazing atmosphere, great owner and team.  Like the selection of beers on tab and the chicken curry from the kitchen.  Burgers are pretty darn good as well!
If you talk to the proprietor of this establishment, "don't mention the war".

This was the starting point of a haunted pub crawl through match.com. They were booked for a private event,  so I will definitely be back for a visit to get the full experience.  The host and staff were amazing!
OUTSTANDING, FRIENDLY, AND EXTREMELY COURTEOUS and Polite.... could NOT have asked for a better place to have the party, If you haven't tried this Pub, you really do need to...
Food was really good n the ghost tour after was awesome.
Really happy with this place. Came on a Sunday for a drink before dinner and the proprietor Colin was bartending. Super friendly guy and had some great jokes. Coming back for the fish & chips 100%

Nice environment. Started out Nightly Spirits Ghost Tour here, showed up an hour early to enjoy a drink. We flustered the wait staff and they ended up combining everyone's bill together. Drinks were good but staff needs to chill and be glad we filled the place.

Just went there for the first time. Really loved everything. Best scotch egg I've had in the city without question. Great beer list and the bartender Jordan was great. Looking forward to many returns.
Great food and great vibe!
Good vibe
Fish and chips are fantastic, and they have a variety of imported beers on tap to match. One of my places to grab food
Friendly service, good drinks, and such a beautiful, historic atmosphere

Love it. Great UK draught beers. Fantastic food, best fish and chips I've ever had. Such a cool relaxing but fun atmosphere.  Owner is the man and super friendly.  Very accommodating for our 1 year old too.  Try neighborhood gem in lincoln park .
Favorite place in Chicago!
Nice, quiet place for a relaxing day.

Finally, a pub that doesn't blast its music. You can actually have a normal conversation while enjoying their extensive selection of spirits. It can get crowded on the weekends but the noise will be from people talking, not yelling at each other over the music.
Awesome ambience and great service
Our server is very efficient, helpful and very polite.
Great atmosphere. Would go back any time
A nicer spot, it's almost like a library with the amount of books it has,. It's an chiller spot for those who don't want to deal with loud music
Great authentic pub.  Had amazing fish and chips.  And my mate enjoyed his Shepard's pie.  Also had a good selection of Scotch and beers.
Good selection of old world beers
Good enough spot for drinks and dinner but don't expect much more than that. Fun location too.

The Red Lion is the best of an English pub in Chicago. They have an excellent selection of beers on tap as well as a great selection of whiskeys. The service is outstanding. Also, the food is very good. The Red Lion is the best blend of a Chicago bar and an English pub.
great service, food, booze, and atmosphere
A true British pub. Amazing beer, great food, and beautiful space. I usually come here in the evenings for a beer or whisky with friends. The two chairs by the fire are the best.
Awesome location in Lincoln Park, interesting and varied beer selection.  Decor is terrifically interesting!
Colin Cordwell is the best publican on this continent.

Really cool British-themed pub in the heart of Lincoln Park. We hung out with some friends and had a good time. Menu is also themed United Kingdom, with a menu full of items such as:  Scotch Egg Poutine (good stuff, get if you can!) Fish n Chips (a safe bet) Irish Nachos English Mac n Cheese (basically Mac n cheese but x10 better)  We easily had no wait on prime one Saturday 7:00pm. Not sure if normal or if we got lucky, going to have to see if we can pull that off next time we come back!
Great beer solection
Honestly the best pretzel I've ever had.

I've hosted two events here, attended a third, and gone for dinner and drinks multiple times. The atmosphere is wonderfully cozy, the food is delicious, the drinks are great and the staff are super friendly and helpful. The historically themed decor is an extra level above and beyond. They have an upper balcony area with a fireplace that you can reserve for 10-12 people and that works great for small gatherings. If you have more than 12, you can reserve the front room, which has a two-sided fireplace and perfectly  imitates a British or Irish pub. For food, I particularly recommend the ploughman's and the pretzel with dipping sauce.
Great place to hang out, have a burger, a beer, a rib roast of beef, or some fish. Very comfortable environment. The onion rings are a specialty.
Great place with amazing atmosphere that is filled with history
Class.
Excellent pub. Very british. Made me feel like home !
First time there was for a Dr who event but the food and decor were amazing

Terrific neighborhood pub with a respectable beer list, and fine authentic food options. Fresh ingredients that are well prepared. Walls, and the owner, are a treasure of history and real life heroes. It's the kind of neighborhood pub Chicago used to be full of, with the owner in site who's ready to be personable and appreciates your business. Great place to hangout with your friends, or bring the family. The kids will learn true history while they eat. Don't miss out on this type of experience.
Nice pub in Lincoln park. Everything you'd expect from a British pub for both food and beverage
Traditional English pub fare.  Always served warm with a good pint.
Beautiful, spacious English pub that features English beers with proper glassware and a cozy fireplace.
Cozy and quiet, at least when we were here. A man was even reading a nook at the bar. Pub food was tasty, not the best ever but enjoyable. We appreciated the mustard selection and the fireplace!

Great pub, the owner Colin is incredibly friendly and very personable. Has a very solid selection of draughts, whiskeys, and makes very good drinks. The food is very good and is a fairly large portion. The Pubs artwork honors those who served in The Great War and WWI. It is a warm and friendly place to grab a drink and relax.
Beautiful English pub. Terrific food and authentic English ales. Plus a warming fire
Great place not too loud interesting crowd

The vibes here are great. Totally love the layout and design. All of the staff was fantastic and attentive (including the owner who was amazingly courteous, helpful, and funny).  Plus, the food -- wow! The reuben I had was phenomenal. I'm not even the biggest fan of corned beef, but I had a feeling they would impress me, and they definitely did. I can't think of a better one I've ever had (if it exists I can't remember it). Plus they loaded me up with a boatload of fries on the side.  Honestly, there's hundreds of places you could go for a beer and a bite in this city, but this place definitely is top tier. I'm excited to bring people back and just soak in more atmosphere.  **If you're going though I highly recommend that reuben. Their other food is fine, but that reuben is on another level**

This is a cozy unpretentious British pub with wonderful food and libations. They have a large list of Scotch whisky and American Bourbon and Rye whiskeys combined with a very good selection of beer and wine by the glass. A local gem in the heart of Lincoln Park.

After waiting at the host station for 10 minutes without being acknowledged we walked to the back and asked the bartender how do we get a table, he condescendingly says "the host station" and walks away. We inform him that we already waited there and he just says "host station" and walks away. At this point a couple spits at the bar open up and we sit down, bartender comes back and says "I told you to go to the host station" and walks away again. We stay put and after a few more minutes he comes back and says the bar area is for a private party so we get up and head back up front. Another ten minutes and the host finally comes to the podium and five more minutes we are seated at a table that had been empty the entire time we have been at this place. I would have left already but my companion really wanted to stay so we did, but I didn't bother ordering nor will I bother returning. Its clear to me they don't value my business.
Nice place with great decor
Quiet, calm, and so so cozy.
Delicious- Grilled cheese with tomato soup.  Great  atmosphere, nice draft beer selection.
They have a good variety of beer. Also enjoyed their Charcuterie board.
Great service and drinks and food.
Fantastic place

Gorgeous atmosphere, and a nice selection of beers and wines. Love the English vibe and decorations, and had a very friendly host/waiter. It’s very standard English fare so don’t look for anything fancy - it is a pub after all. It’s also very quiet for a pub although we came on a Wednesday night so it could be busier/louder on the weekends.
Love this place!

Awesome! Fish and chips great! Shepherd's pie delicious! Scotch eggs, OMG! These guys have absolutely fantastic food and an incredible beer selection. I would be a regular here if they were anywhere near my home. I will be back the next time I'm in the area and I recommend anyone and everyone go.
Good! They tried to accommodate our large party very well. But they were understaffed, and the chicken sandwich was only ok. The beers we're Great! But low alcohol.
The bar feels like an old English library, it's a really cool setting!

Awesome food and a solid beer selection. Everything from the pretzel to the bangers and mash are to die for. Go and sit at the bar some time to talk to Colin, he's the type of man who meets you once and remembers your name years later... not to mention he tells some wicked storied. Andrews also pretty stellar. Just go!

This place has delicious food! They’ve got a good selection of comfort food, like fish n chips, nachos, sandwiches, poutine... I had a good time, everyone was very nice. And they have the best decor! It’s such a cute location that has a good atmosphere. Right next to DePaul and the Fullerton Red Line stop.
Owner is a super cool guy, the service is absolutely impeccable. Would definitely recommend to anyone looking to have a good time.
One of the nicest pubs in Chicago.  Great staff and owner.  Great food and atmosphere.

Not sure what was up tonight. Was invited by a friend while visiting Chicago.  From the outset, the server (guy, short blond hair) seemed to be in a bad mood. They had a special, with a beer and meal. I simply asked if I could let him know the beer in just a moment, as I wanted to put in the food in a timely manner. This, and everything else, seemed like such an inconvenience.  He was friendly to everyone around us, so I’m not sure if we did something to upset him or something. For the record, I still tipped over 15%.  I tried to say thank you and goodnight, but he ignored our group on the way out.  Extra star for the food.
Standard pub fare with a nod towards a more British options. Good service.
If you're coming from the UK it's like a home from home. Real little hidden gem, food you can't fault & the friendliest service you could want. Can't recommend it high enough 👍👍
Very good food and wonderful atmosphere . Very friendly service.
Great food and service!!

Really great atmoshpere! I felt in the beginning of the 20th century. They serve great beers and good fish&chips! What else ? The barman is really nice and we can really feel the neighborhood life in that place! Go there when you are in the neighborhood ;)
Very friendly staff. I highly recommend the 2 Towns Ginja Ninja cider
Bring your A game for history and puns.

A very interesting eclectic bar with a terrific staff and perfectly friendly and genuine owner full of stories about the place, design and history. Quite a funny guy too. Drinks were great, as well. Awesome location.
Amazing interior...looks like a legit English pub. Great burger... Super reasonable prices.

Great atmosphere and a wide selection of drinks. I've been here when it was busy and I still had a great experience. The food is AMAZING. I took my parents here and they've traveled all over Europe and they loved it here. I also visited during a less busy time and it was just as good of an experience. I would definitely recommend this place to everyone!
The menu isn't extensive, but I did like the food and decor.

A very good british pub with all the requisites. It is a beautiful place with obvious tlc.  A good upstairs and a front sittin room. Pleanty of nooks for groups or watching soccer or reading a book with your pint
The beer selection is amazing for an English Pub. I had the Sheppard's Pie and it was amazing. I will definitely be going back soon.
The inside of this place looks fantastic and the food and drinks were very good.
Food was great, service was spotty.
This British inspired pub has old-world charm, and historical references. The food is fine, and the imported English ale is tasty.
Good food. Solid British beer selection. Even smells like a pub in Britain, somehow. I think all the old books, maybe.
Great place...great ww1 pictures..good service...good food...cozy fireplace upstairs...clean bathrooms
Good selection of beer. I would recommend the scotch eggs.
Food was no good

I was there on a weeknight so it wasn't crowded at all. I was meeting some friends to play a card game. Not very well lit unfortunately, but I won't hold that against them. I imagine I'd hate this place on a busy night, but I don't like bars. So my opinion is skewed.
Super cool place in my FAVORITE Chicago neighborhoood. This place is cool.
Good atmosphere, knowledgeable staff
Great food. Great service.

Great food and an amazing atmosphere. Very friendly staff. A library with a fun theme, drinks and food. Great place to socialize as the music and sounds are not too loud and overpowering. The beer selection is also as good as their whiskey selection. A lot of history displayed throughout the place using pictures.
Great place, great service, English feeling
Great restaurant and a fun pub. Not too loud and a very friendly staff.

This is my favorite bar in Chicago!  It has a very relaxed atmosphere. Only one TV in the bar which almost always has the sound off. The employees are really friendly, and the owner has read and can talk about all the books that line the walls. This is a great bar for a date or just to read a book. It is very quite and relaxed with a fantastic whisky selection. I highly recommend it!

The atmosphere is my favorite part of this pub. It's got bookshelves and books on the upper level, and a fireplace, with dark wood tones and warm lighting. It's very homey. I love to come here for a casual, relaxing bar experience. They have a large selection of drinks available,  including a few ciders of which I am a fan of, and a restaurant sized menu for food and dining. Food is a little pricey, but it doesn't altogether matter to me because I don't go there for the food. The bartenders are friendly, and may be willing to give you a walk through of the alcohol available if you ask!
Charming pub with food and drink options.

Very interesting location I love the the fusion of library and bar and anglophilia,. Ghost tour the ghost tour starts there I believe. The drinks are great however you have to know it's more of a whiskey bar so they don't have like everything, but at least the bartender that was there when I was there works really well with you to find something you like.  The Manhattan that one person had was delicious the wine the wine was delicious. The Baileys Irish Cream was delicious.
Wonderful pub with great atmosphere and fish and chips

The Red Lion superbly maintains my two favorite pub traditions: excellent ales and the art of conversation. Whether listening to the owner, staff, or guests, you can always enjoy hearing interesting conversations which often invite others to participate and share. In particular, the upstairs is an ideal setting for group discussions: it is cozy and quiet, and has been very hospitable to my/our Philosophy groups.
Love the drafts and ambiance
The staff here are awesome. Chris and Andrew are great guys and work very hard for their customers.

One of a kind Chicago institution.  Colin Cordwell, the owner, is part librarian, part trivia master, part bartender extraordinaire, and all-around wonderful host.  The space is beautiful, the food/draft both excellent, and the absence of the fraternity/sorority crowd so prevalent on this stretch of Lincoln Ave. is welcome indeed!
Great spot for whisky.  Really cool decor.
Haunted
The pub itself and the host are historical gems.

Very disappointed, with the food and service. I had reservations for 7 pm, they had one table by the door. I ordered a chicken burger, tasted like it was cooked in peanut oil way to long and my bun was soggy. Also, they had no music playing in the bar. Overall, horrible experience will not go back.
Great English pub.  A classic.

Great pub!  Very cozy and comfortable setting - it’s like sitting in the library of Downton Abbey - a fireplace, lots of books, historical photos, and British nick backs. The food and beverages were excellent. I highly recommend this place!
Gives you the vibes of being in Britian. My husband is British and he was happy to be there.
Nice spot for a drink and some fish and chips
A Chicago gem. Great place for good beer and conversation.
Loved the corn beef brisket.  Great beer selection.  Bit pricey but is an upper scale place.  I would go back to try other meals and of course  more beer

This is a hidden gem! Super well done English pub. I haven’t gone here without meeting someone new. Quiet and intimate with very cool decor. You feel like you’re in Europe. Locals come here to meet up with friends and enjoy a mature evening.
Enjoyed the nitro beers, and chill pub atmosphere
Shepherd's pie!

Sorry to say my experience was very disappointing. But then my visit was under somewhat unusual circumstances. We were a group of about 10 coming in after a special church event early afternoon, Super Bowl Sunday, in a snow storm.  Except for one couple we were the only people there. Everyone else had gone in and ordered before I arrived, as I was searching for a place to park for quite a while. One of our party mentioned to me that the waiter was  "surly" at first. But I was not there at the time and could only notice that his manner improved the closer we got to tip time. Most everyone ordered eggs of some sort, which did look delicious. But there was a long wait before the first 2 orders arrived and equally long waits between orders arriving after that, which came in groups of 2. Since I was late I only ordered 2 margaritas. However when the checks came the gentleman who was paying for his 2 drinks and mine was surprised to find how expensive the drinks were. He said he should have told them to use the house liquor, as they had used the most expensive instead. (I know Patron was used in my drink. And I didn't really enjoy it that much.)
Pub grub.  Well done with a tasty beer list.  I like dark beers.  They have a twist on a black and tan.  I like the atmosphere as well.  Books and a fireplace.  Very homey.
Homey atmosphere, friendly staff, and amazing bar food. Best poutine I've ever had!
Food was good and a nice selection of beers.
This place is a must-visit place when you are in the area. If you're able to meet the owner you will never want to leave the place and sit there and listen to him spin Yarns
Really nice relaxed Pub good hearty English Fare
Awesome scotch list
It was great a great place. It has this old time feel to it. Loved the drinks as well.
Fun higher-end feeling pub that reminded us of some of the nice pubs we hit up in London. Great beer and liquor selection and tasty pub grub. Full-English was great!
Such a cozy space, and such a friendly staff. A really nice spot to spend an evening with friends, especially in the artic Chicago winter.
Unique place! I liked this bar and the owner was great!
Awesome place. Great food. Burgers we awesome.
Very inviting, warm atmosphere with well prepared food.
A true adult bar
A must visit in Lakeview
The owner (Colin) could not be any more friendly or hospitable. The interior is beautiful, warm, and authentic. Didn't have a chance to try the food, but we'll be back!
Friendly Warm personable Atmosphere
Great owner/operator/barman in Colin.  Service and food never disappoint.
Great atmosphere, fresh baked muffins were heavenly.

I took my parents here for dinner last night. The service was quick and friendly. Good beer selection. Excellent English food choices...I had the fish and chips and it was delicious. The walls of the pub are decorated with real WWII memorabilia, and the owner of the place even came to our table to tell us facts about some of the photos. The cozy atmosphere here is right up my alley; the fireplaces are a great touch. I will definitely be going there often from now on.

Fun authentic English Pub in Lincoln Park. One of the only places in the city that serves Old Speckled Hen on tap. Tons of other English beers available too. Had the Scotch Eggs an popcorn. Food was acceptable.
Awesome pub feel!  Just no staff at all so slow service. The delish food was surprising.  Shepherds pie and Welsh rarebit... well done!
Its great and the service is good!

Came in for a quick drink. Kitchen was closed and waitress offered us popcorn. We took her up on the offer and was provided a small plate of popcorn and a bill for $6. No bar on the planet would charge for this. Not impressed.
The ambiance was great, the beer selection was good, the food was OK. I'll probably stop by again at some point and I might revise the review.
Great old fashioned place with good beer and delicious food.
Staff were very nice! Just came for some nice drinks while in Chicago. Love the area as well!
Cozy pub. "The last adult bar in Lincoln Park" mentioned by some.
Great burgers and cozy bookcases, bottled drinks were good, but watch out for the bartender: watered down drinks really kill the mood

What an amazing place! A lot of WWI and WWII pictures and a very impressive book collection! Great drinks. The place was quiet when we went and had a chance to talk to the owner. The drawings in the back were made by the owner's father while he was at a German POW camp in WWII. The bartender was also a very likable guy.
Nice historical landmark and decent food!
My favorite English Pub.  Colin, the owner, makes you feel right at home
Great atmosphere!! The food is fantastic and the staff is genuinely friendly!
Nice replica of an English Pub, but alas the food is mediocre.
Neat

Fantastic experience, make double sure you visit this pub while in Chicago. (Arguably the best pub in Chicago/ maybe England) The owner rebuilt his fathers pub, who was the only person to escape as a German POW during WW2. Made legendary in the movie the great escape. The current owner is also more than happy to share the  history he knows.  Ask him about the time his Nan knocked him out!
I love this bar! The owner actually works behind the bar! He's got a lot of amazing stories and he cares about his clientele! The food is amazing and they take very good care of you here!!!
Food was not hot
I'm a big night cap guy. Collin makes the best night caps
Great pub with a fine draft selection
One of my favourite pubs in Chicago, or possibly on the entire planet.  Colin the owner is a legend in his own right.
Great vibe, was very chill on a friday night. Bartenders were cool and the food was good!
A true english gem in Chicago...great food..great staff and a great owner with Collin.
Great atmosphere. I had the vegetable curry and it was delicious.

Cozy, homely with a wonderful atmosphere and Host!  A great collection of European Beers, British Food (pretty damn good too!) and an interesting history.  Colin, the Host has done an amazing job with the place and has some curious tales to tell. Kudos to him!  Will go there over and over again! Cheers!
My favorite pub in the city. Wonderful quaint atmosphere with great English food and beer selection.
Great beer selection! Food was good, a bit expensive.
Cozy and warm environment. I love the fireplace, and all the books.
Nice looking bar, nice place to sit and chat with friends around a table or by the fire.... mixed crowd from the suits to guys in jeans and t-shirt.
The staff and bartenders were friendly and attentive. They also have an excellent draft list along with a great environment to enjoy them in.
The magic show is the best
Been awhile since I've been there. Still haunted?

You don't have to be super dressy although you definitely can be. Great atmosphere and friendly staff. The beer options are just as European as the decor but after a short talk with the bartender he found me the perfect drink!
Went there to catch up a friend. The place is not overly noisy. The food was decent. I would go there again for a beer and discussion and probably somewhere else for food.

Whiskey for days, vintages that you don't see at other bars. Old red lion was like drinking in an old comfy shoe. New red lion is like drinking in a comfy wool knit cardigan and fresh slippers. It feels new but in the way that you know it's quality will last and get better with age. Knowledgeable bar staff that won't brush off your questions about the decor. In fact, from my experience, they happily indulge in offering information about European history that you would never learn anywhere else in Chicago. Good whiskey and great conversation make this a gem for anyone with an open mind and a sincere thirst for history.
Not bad
Nice, cozy, open space in the heart of Lincoln Park.
I LOVE this place, it has so much history, excellent beer, great food options, and the wittiest and most pleasant staff ever.
Fabulous bar and decor. Homey English pub with good food. Always a must stop before heading home on a weekend night.
Walked in, sat at the bar for 7ish minutes, bartender ignored us the whole time and just talked to the people right next to us. Only 6-7 people were there - not busy. We left.

Yes. Enjoy the renaissance of the Red Lion. If you meet Colin and lucky enough to have a conversation with him, you'll notice he is truly Lincoln Park gentry. He's been there since DePaul had to hang up riot proof shutters on the English Department building.
British pub, the inside decor makes you feel like you are in a library . Definitely worth checking out.
Good food. Good service. Adult atmosphere.

Truly, a great pub.  Beautifully appointed with a mid-century British feel.  Great menu, great bar selection in a warm, inviting, rich atmosphere; if you can’t enjoy yourself here the problem is with you.
No, the game is not on in here. Yay!

Chicago's Best Tavern with proprietor Colin Cordwell aka "First Lord of Chicago Barkeeps" always the gracious host who makes you feel more than welcome....that you belong. Food excellent with highlights being Cottage Pie, Fish & Chips, and Bangors & Mash.
Really nice décor and a good selection of drinks on offer. The bar staff were very friendly and enjoyed discussing their choice of drinks!

Amazing place and wonderful atmosphere,  I highly recommend this location to anyone looking for a good drink and amazing poutine. The fish and chips portion is huge and delicious while the bangers and mash disappeared quickly from my husband's plate. We will definitely be back soon!

Great LP pub. Wonderfully decorated interior that really transports you out of Chicago and over to Britain. Food is great, and again, adds to the well done English feel of the place with traditional dishes you wouldn't find in any old Chicago restaurant. Absolutely worth stopping in!

What a great spot.  So very adult!  Clubby atmosphere with authentic WWII pix and memorabilia.  Book cases - with real books.  Bi-level, fireplace and comfy chairs.  English Pub food done well.  Great place to go when you want to have a conversation without yelling across the table to be heard.  Great asset to the neighborhood.
This place is great.  The upstairs fireplace is awesome in the winter.  The guy that owns this place might be the best car tender in Chicago, he knows his stuff and has the X factor of passion.

I am married to a Brit and lived in London for 4 years myself and this is the most authentic pub that exists in Chicago.  It's a Marston's pub so you get Pedigree and other ales and bitters.  And the food is really good - better than what you'd expect from pub food for sure.   We had the Scotch egg, which was very nicely done.  Then went for Suffolk Ham Charcuterie and this was bliss.  Finished off with the Vindaloo Chicken sandwich which was an Indian on bread.  Unusual and filling.  The staff are really friendly and the pub has been overhauled and it's ornate and beautiful.  Great spot to pop in for a drink and good food or to hang out for the evening.
